[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Mastering Fundamentals"]
[Black "What is a rook lift and when should we go for it?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bd6 5. Nbd2 O-O 6. c3 c5 7. Bd3 Qc7 8. Bxd6
Qxd6 9. Ne5 Nc6 10. f4 b6 11. O-O Bb7
{ This is a typical position that can be found in the chapter Queen's Gambit Declined with a quick ...e6, ...Bd6. }
12. Rf3
{ The rooks are incredibly powerful pieces once they reach an open file. Currently, there are no open files available, but White has this golden opportunity to play Rf3 with the idea to go Rh3 ➼ attacking Black's king. This typical maneuver is called a 'rook lift' and it's a very useful tool in the Carlsbad structure and also in the Reversed stonewall. }
