[Black "What is an open file & how can we use it?"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r5k1/pp3ppp/3qpn2/3p4/8/3PP3/PPRN1PPP/3Q2K1 b - - 0 2"]
[SetUp "1"]

2... Qd7 { This is a position coming from the 'Copycat' chapter. } 3. Qc1
{ The last move secured the open file because Black was threatening to play ...Rc8 with full equality. After the last move, White is clearly better and the only side who can push for a win because we are controlling the open file.But why are open files so important? First of all, an open file is a file that has no pawns on it. Secondly, open files can more effectively be used by the long-range heavy pieces @@StartBracket@@rooks/queens@@EndBracket@@. The open file is very important because it gives us the chance to infiltrate the enemy camp and create a lot of annoying threats. Typically, the best square to enter the enemy camp is on the 7th rank @@StartBracket@@or on the 2nd rank if you are playing as Black@@EndBracket@@. }
