{ In this position, we can see why pushing the a-pawn is such a powerful tool in the London System. White is able to win the game by simply having more space and a dangerous pawn on a6! The a6-pawn is usually very annoying for Black when White can either attack the a7-pawn or has tactical ideas like in our case with Bxb6 motifs. You have to consider these factors constantly; otherwise, this strategy can backfire sometimes, and the a6-pawn will remain a bit overextended and turn into a weakness. }
1. Bxb6
{ This small tactical trick gives white a winning endgame ➼ clearing the path for the a-pawn. }
