[Black "Copycat: 5... Bg6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3
{ This is the most precise move ➼ avoiding the annoying  2.Bf4  c5!  which gives us some headaches as explained in this informational. }
2... Nf6 3. Bf4 Bf5 4. e3 e6
{ 4...c6  would transpose to the Slav Defense Chapter. } 5. Bd3
{ The simplest and most effective way of dealing with the ...Bf5 lines in general. Black can now choose between:   5...Bxd3 @@StartBracket@@the most popular move@@EndBracket@@  5...Bg6 @@StartBracket@@the flexible move@@EndBracket@@  5...Ne4 @@StartBracket@@using our favorite plan against us!@@EndBracket@@  5...Bd6 @@StartBracket@@the 'copy-cat'@@EndBracket@@. }
5... Bg6 6. Ne5
{ With the idea to play Nxg6 ➼ collecting the bishop pair with a small edge for White. Keep in mind that we are going to castle O-O because Black doesn't have any realistic attacking chances on the h-file. }
6... Bxd3 7. cxd3
{ With an extra tempo for White compared to the normal lines because we have managed to play Ne5. You can find more information about this structure in the Typical Pawn Structure chapter: Doubled d-pawns. }
