[Black "The Slav endgame"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c6 4. e3 Bf5 5. c4 e6 6. Qb3 Qb6 7. c5 Qxb3 8. axb3
Nbd7 9. Nc3 a6 10. b4 Rc8 11. h3 Be7 12. Nd2
{ The start of White's key maneuver ➼ preparing to play Nb3-Na5 which targets the weakest spot in Black's camp @@StartBracket@@the b7-pawn@@EndBracket@@. Black's main defense is to meet Nb3 with ...Bd8 and against Na5 to play ...Bxa5. For a better understanding of this structure, make sure to check out the Theory Chapter and the model endgames between Grachev-Rychagov, 2010 and Nikolic-Piket, 1989. For now, I will just introduce you to some of the main ideas for both sides.   Typical plans for Black:  ...Bd8-Bc7  ...Bd8 and wait to play ...Bxa5 when White goes Na5  ...Nh5 @@StartBracket@@when White does not have h3 on the board@@EndBracket@@  ...O-O-Bd8-Rfe8 and break with ...e5!   Typical plans for White:  Nd2-Nb3-Na5 @@StartBracket@@the most important plan@@EndBracket@@  always meeting ...Bxa5 with bxa5!, followed by Ra4-Rb4  expand on the kingside with g4  Kd2/O-O ➼ making Black's ...e5-break less effective  when Black goes ...e5 we have a choice between Bh2 and dxe5, followed by Nd4. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Typical Pawn Structures"]
[Black "The Carlsbad with Bd3"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 cxd4 6. exd4 Bf5 7. c3 e6 8.
Qb3 Qc8 9. Nh4 Bg6 10. Nxg6 hxg6 11. Bd3 Be7 12. O-O O-O 13. Rae1
{ This is a very typical position for the Carlsbad structure. In this particular case, White is clearly better because of the bishop pair and also thanks to the g6-hook, which will speed up our attack. For more details, you can check out the model game between Iturrizaga Bonelli,E @@StartBracket@@2673@@EndBracket@@-Gomez,J @@StartBracket@@2481@@EndBracket@@ Ho Chi Minh City 2017. Now I will just give you an overview of what are the main plans for both sides.   Standard gameplan for White:  Nf3-Ne5 @@StartBracket@@both recaptures are interesting and depend on the position@@EndBracket@@  Qd1 is a powerful move to bring back the queen over the kingside  ideas to rook lift with Re3-Rh3  expand on the kingside with g3-h4 followed by Kg2-Rh1 ➼ preparing the h5-break  generally, we can slow down Black's minority attack with a3.  Standard plans for Black:  The Minority Attack @@StartBracket@@pushing ...a6-b5-b4@@EndBracket@@ ➼ weakening the c3-pawn  ...a6-b5, followed by ...Na5-Nc4 and potentially maneuvering with ...Nd6-Nde4/Nf5  ...Bd8-Bc7 ➼ trading pieces is generally a good strategy while defending  ...Rd8-Bd6 ➼ as seen in the model game between Kamsky-Shirov, 2018. }
