{ This is the most common move for Black because generally people can't live for long with the e5-knight. They have to chop it! }
10. fxe5 { Capturing towards the center and attacking the f6-knight. } 10...
Nd7 11. Qh5
{ Threatening Qxh7 and forcing Black to create a weakness ➼ This is a typical theme for the London System.  11...f5  is met by the typical  12.g4!  and @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/1ppn1ppp/p3p3/3pP2Q/3P4/2PB4/PP1N1PPP/R3K2R b KQ - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11...h6  12.Nf3  followed by g4-g5 is also very promising for White @@StartBracket@@taking advantage of the h6-hook@@EndBracket@@. }
11... g6 12. Qh6
{ Here you can notice why delaying O-O was important for White ➼ we have an additional option of going for h4-h5 with a crushing attack. We can put the same position but with O-O and White is still much better, so you don't have to worry too much about the move by move stuff! }
