{ Threatening to play c3 and get away with the two extra pawns. } 13... Qb4+
{ Winning back the b2-pawn. } 14. Nd2 Qxb2 15. a4
{ With an extra pawn for White which happens to be an outside passed pawn! We can continue with O-O followed by Nb3-a5 and Black has to defend for the rest of the game. }
