1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 Bf5 4. e3 e6 5. Bd3
{ In this chapter, we are dealing with one of Black's best lines ➡ 'The Copycat' line. I recommend sticking with the more positional approach and recapturing back on  d3  with the pawn. The alternative  5.c4  is more ambitious, but also riskier as explained in the informational. After @@StartFEN@@rn1qkb1r/ppp2ppp/4pn2/3p1b2/3P1B2/4PN2/PPP2PPP/RN1QKB1R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Bd3  the material will be split in:  •  5...Bxd3   •  5...Bg6   •  5...Bd6   •  5...Ne4    Usually, this variation will lead to the 'Doubled pawns structure' which should definitely be studied carefully in order to be a successful London player.  Model games arising from this chapter:  ➡ Muthaiah Al-Hakobyan Eduard, Abu Dhabi 2018 }
