{ There was nothing wrong with the natural  9.Nc3  ,  but Korobov is preparing to reinforce the e5-knight with Ndf3, which is a very interesting idea that took Mamedyarov by surprise. }
9... O-O 10. Qf3
{ The queen is heading towards h3, from where it will support White's kingside play. This is a common maneuver in the London System, and we see it more often with the light squared bishops on the board. Nevertheless, here is at least as strong. }
10... Qc7
{ This was Mamedyarov's choice ➼ defending the d6-bishop before playing ...Nbd7 so there won't be any Nxc6 tricks! }
11. Qh3
{ The queen has reached the optimal square, and next it will be knight's turn to join the kingside party. }
11... Nbd7 12. Ndf3
{ Reinforcing the e5-knight. Now that White has a firm grip over the center, we can safely start launching the attack. }
12... Rfe8 13. g4
{ Black has not made any obvious mistakes, but little by little White has managed to gain strong control over the center and now we are ready to launch a deadly storm on the kingside. For more details on how to follow up the initiative, make sure to check out the game between Korobov,A @@StartBracket@@2688@@EndBracket@@-Mamedyarov,S @@StartBracket@@2764@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2020. }
