6. Bd2
{ This may be not enough for an objective advantage, but for sure it's going to shock your opponent. On a good day we might even trap their queen! }
6... Qxc4 7. e4
{ The point! White gets a strong center while Black has problems finding a safe square for the queen. }
7... Qe6 { This is Black's best try. } 8. Ng5
{ Attacking the e6-queen and the h5-knight! } 8... Qg6 9. e5
{ With a big threat of playing Bd3 ➼ White has the initiative despite Black being able to defend with perfect play. Keep in mind this is a very fresh position with no games played, and your opponent will be unprepared. }
