10. Bg3 { Creating a big threat of e4 because ...Nxc3 will be met by exf5! }
10... Nxc3 { The simplest solution for Black. } 11. Qxc3
{ I like taking with the queen here because  11.bxc3  c5  seems to give Black an easy game. So instead we keep the extra space and try to attack Black on the queenside with the minority attack. }
11... Nd7 12. Be2 Nf6 13. Nd2 { With the positional threat of playing f3-e4. }
13... Ne4 14. Nxe4 Bxe4 15. f3 Bg6 16. O-O
{ The position should be close to equal, but to me it feels like White is playing for two results with the minority attack. }
16... Rd8 17. b4 Qd7 18. a4
{ We will eventually push b5 and Black has to be careful. } *

