{ This is the most common move order for Black in both OTB and online chess. }
8. Rc1
{ This line has an insane potential to give you a quick win according to my experience and what people do on average in the database. Even strong players have failed to avoid the upcoming deadly traps.   In case you are a fan of slower play, there is a good alternative in going  8.h3  followed by Be2 and O-O with a pleasant position. }
8... Be7
{ This is by far the most common move in the position.   I should also mention  8...dxc4  ,  which avoids the quick disaster than can happen after cxd5 followed by Nb5, but White keeps a pleasant position after  9.Bxc4  Be7  10.O-O  O-O  11.Rfe1⩲  when White is slightly better thanks to the opportunity to expand in the center with e4. One cool trick that you want to keep in mind is that  11...Ne4  can be met by  12.Nxe4  Bxe4  13.Bxe6! }
