9... Nxd5
{ The best move for Black, putting pressure on the f4-bishop. Funnily enough, this is only played in 1 out of 10 games, according to my experience and the online stats. }
10. Bg3
{ We are keeping the tension, and the plan is to push e4 in the future. } 10...
O-O
{ The most natural move, but a big mistake!   10...Nxc3  is the safer/better move, avoiding the direct threat of going e4. After  11.bxc3  O-O  12.Be2⩲  White  gets a pleasant position. We are going to castle short next and then a typical plan is to play Nd2 followed by f3-e4 with a slightly better position thanks to the extra space in the center. }
11. e4
{ Of course, White can also play the simple  11.Be2  and get a playable game, but why not punish Black when we can? }
