{ This was played by Jobava, but White has a funny way to hide the king. } 14.
Kd1 fxe6 15. Bd3
{ We will kick the bishop with a3 and then Kc2-Kb1 will bring our king to its ideal square. After the king reaches safety on b1 we can start attacking the weak e6-pawn. }
