{ The key move to grab the initiative, forcing Black to take on b3, giving us the upper hand on the queenside. Now you can fully understand why it was so important to play 5. c4 instead of the 'automatic' 5.c3-move that we see most of the time in the London.   Keep in mind that you want to force your opponent to take on b3 and open up the a-file for the rook, otherwise there is no point in going for the early queen trade.  7.Qxb6?!  axb6∞  would already give Black a very comfortable position, so it should be avoided! }
