[Black "The quick 3...e6/4...Bd6 - 5.Ne5!? alternative #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3
{ This is the most precise move ➼ avoiding the annoying  2.Bf4  c5!  which gives us some headaches as explained in this informational. }
2... Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bd6 5. Ne5
{ This could be a viable alternative to the main move  5.Nbd2  if you are trying to avoid the doubled pawns/want to mix it up a bit. }
5... O-O 6. Nd2 c5 7. c3
{ Preparing to play Bd3 so we can meet ...c4 with Bc2! } 7... Nc6 8. Bd3 Qc7
{ Putting pressure on the e5-square. } 9. Ndf3
{ Reinforcing the e5-knight! At this point Black has a choice between:  9...b6  9...Nd7  9...Ne4  9... cxd4. }
9... Ne4
{ This is one of the main drawbacks for us. We have managed to get good control over the e5-square, but in the process we have lost a bit of control over the e4-square. Black is threatening to push ...f6 on the next move. }
10. Bg3
{ Initially I quite liked  10.Qc2!?  ➼ but then realized it is much simpler to play Bg3 against both 9...Ne4 and 9...cxd4 10.exd4 Ne4! }
10... f6 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Bxe4
