{ This has to be played because  13...f5  allows  14.dxc5  ➼ winning a pawn. }
14. hxg3 cxd4 15. cxd4
{ Opening up the c-file so we can put pressure on the c-pawn by playing Rc1! }
15... f5 { Protecting the e4-pawn. } 16. O-O
{ We can continue with Rc1 next with long term pressure on the c6-pawn. } *

