7... O-O { This is the most common move for Black. } 8. Bd3 Qc7
{ This is a very common mistake. Black is preparing to push ...e5, but this simply doesn't work tactically. }
9. dxc5
{ It's very easy to forget about this move! White is simply up a pawn. } 9...
Bxg3 10. hxg3 e5 { Threatening to push ...e4! } 11. e4
{ After this critical move we can safely stop and claim that White should be much better with the extra pawn and the open h-file which gives us good attacking prospects on the kingside. }
