9. h4
{ This is a pretty common theme for our repertoire and also White's best try against Benjamin's line. He does an amazing job in covering and explaining a brand new position while also covering interesting novelties for White. There is not really that much I can add since he did a fantastic job, but we can go a bit deeper with the analysis where he stops. }
