[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "7) Queen's Gambit Declined without 5…e6"]
[Black "Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. Nbd2
{ In this chapter, we are focusing on the ...c5 main lines when Black plays with the light squared bishop outs. The material will be split between:  •  5...Bg4   •  5...Bf5   •  5...cxd4   •  5...Nh5    Typical pawn structures arising from this chapter:  • Carlsbad with Bd3
• Carlsbad with Be2
• Carlsbad with h3-g4
Model games arising from this chapter:  ➡ Bachmann Axel-Hong Andrew, Philadelphia 2017  ➡ Iturrizaga Bonelli Eduardo-Gomez John Paul, Ho Chi Minh City 2017  ➡ Limbert Neil-Mueller Gerhard, Correspondence 2016  ➡ Carlsen Magnus-Caruana Fabiano, Lichess Rapid 2020  ➡ Kamsky Gata-Shirov Alexei, St. Petersburg 2018  ➡ Berkes Ferenc-McShane Luke, Heraklion 2017  ➡ Berkes Ferenc-Nguyen Thai Dai Van, Zalakaros 2016  ➡ Kravtsiv Martyn-Mchedlishvili Mikheil, Turkey 2019  Typical endgames arising from this chapter:  ➡ Miles Anthony John-Nogueiras Santiago Jesus, Varadero 2000  ➡ Tang Andrew-Ali Marandi Cemil Can, chess.com 2019  ➡ Nihal Sarin-Checa Nicolas, chess.com 2021  ➡ Kamsky Gata-Quintiliano Pinto Renato Rodrigues, chess.com 2021  ➡ CountLondon-alexkous2000, chess.com 2022 }
