8. Nh4
{ This was recently implemented by Aronian and Demchenko. This is the most serious attempt to put the ...Bg4-lines under a question mark. White's plan is to advance on the kingside with h3-g4 and win the bishop pair.   An alternative could be  8.h3  followed by g4 which could lead to similar positions, but I prefer 8.Nh4 because it avoids ...Bf5. }
