{ This move is very popular in online chess. My guess is that people underestimate White's initiative in the upcoming endgames. }
8. Ne5
{ After deeply analysing all the alternatives, this strikes me as by far the best chance for White. I experienced quite a lot of games with  8.Qxb6  axb6  9.Bb5  which is slightly more pleasant for White and can be 'an easy fix' if you are lazy, but my winrate was around 50%.   Since I started playing the precise  8.Ne5!  I win most of my games in this line, and I've noticed that most of the Black players are unable to react properly. Even those who find the best defence will suffer in the long run in these lines. }
8... Nxe5 9. Qxb6 { The most precise, even though  9.dxe5  is also not bad! }
9... axb6 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Bb5
{ Creating a very unpleasant pin. The next step of the plan is to break with e4. }
11... O-O-O
