1. d4 d5 2. Nf3
{ This is the most precise move ➼ avoiding the annoying  2.Bf4  c5!  which gives us some headaches as explained in this informational. }
2... Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. Nbd2
{ This is the key move to start with. A common mistake that most of the London System players make is  5.c3  allowing  5...Qb6  with a good version for Black. }
5... cxd4 6. exd4 Bf5 7. c3
{ I prefer to stick with the standard approach, but if you are willing to mix it up, you can try  7.Bb5  which is connected with Ne5-ideas like in the game between Firouzja-Anton Guijarro, Wijk and Zee 2021. The main reason why I like to stick with  7.c3  ➼ is because it fits better with our repertoire overall. }
7... e6
{ The most common move ➼ preparing to develop the dark-squared bishop and castle short. }
8. Qb3
{ Attacking the b7-pawn ➼ This is a common theme when Black develops the light-squared bishop in the ...c5 lines. }
8... Qd7
{ This is not the best square for the queen because Black may have some problems connected with White's bishop developing to b5.   The line  8...Bd6!  became very fashionable recently thanks to the super computers which indicated that Black has very decent compensation after  9.Qxb7  Bxf4  10.Qxc6+  Kf8  with an unclear game. My conclusion was that White has a few lines to test Black's memory, but not more than that. For this reason I suggest we stick with a more practical approach:  9.Bxd6  Qxd6  10.Be2  O-O  11.O-O  with a typical Carlsbad position.  11...Rab8  Threatening to push ...b5!  12.a4!  Taking space on the queenside and stopping the minority attack.  12...Rfc8  13.h3  h6  14.Rfe1  Making small, useful moves all the time.  14...Qd8  15.Qa3  Nd7  16.b4⩲  White had an easier position and won a smooth game in Bachmann,A @@StartBracket@@2653@@EndBracket@@-Hong,A @@StartBracket@@2383@@EndBracket@@ Philadelphia 2017. }
9. Ne5
{ This move is very unpleasant for Black! Surprisingly enough, Black is still relatively okay after  9...Qc8  where I recommend  10.Bd3  with an easier game for White, but according to the stats ➼ most of the players will fall for the trap. }
9... Nxe5 { Eliminating the annoying knight seems logical right? } 10. dxe5
{ After this important move White wins at least a piece. } 10... Ne4 11. Bb5
{ Winning Black's queen. } *

