{ Preparing to push g4 ➼ this is the only try for an edge. } 7... Be7 8. g4
{ Since Black has more space on the queenside, we have to push on the kingside. }
8... O-O 9. h4 Nc6 10. h5 { Preparing g5 followed by g6! } 10... Qd8 11. Bg2
{ With good attacking prospects on the kingside based on the g5-g6 pawn break. }
