7. Ba3 e6 8. e3 Nbd7
{ Trying to win back the c5-pawn immediately.  8...Ne4  doesn't really help because White gets the initiative after  9.c4! }
9. c6
{ The pawn is very loose on c6, but it's very annoying for Black! A typical trick is that  9...Bxa3  loses on the spot after  10.cxd7+!  @@StartBracket@@intermezzo@@EndBracket@@ followed by Nxa3 with an extra piece for White. }
9... bxc6 10. bxc6 { Attacking the d7-knight. } 10... Nc5 11. Qd4
{ Attacking the c5-knight. } 11... Qb6
{ Protecting the c5-knight and attacking the c6-pawn. } 12. Nbd2 Qxc6 13. Rb1
{ Creating a huge threat of Bb5 with a very promising position for White with a nice lead in development. }
