{ Black has an alternative in  6...d6  . The idea behind this move is to play a waiting game with ...Nbd7 and ...h6 ➼ hoping that White will castle short and then ...g5!? becomes annoying to deal with. This line does not have any theoretical value, but I thought it might be useful to include since I ran into the ...g5 plan a couple of times and I had a hard time dealing with it OTB. The key idea to counter this setup as White is to simply wait a bit before castling!  7.Bd3  Nbd7  . Now  8.c3!  is a very clever waiting move. We are inviting Black to castle short, so we can safely do the same and avoid the ...g5 nonsense.   8.O-O  I made this move automatically in a few blitz games, and quickly found myself in trouble after the following moves:  8...h6  9.e4!  g5  10.Bg3  g4  11.hxg4  Nxg4  12.Qe2  h5∞  With a complicated position, where Black is getting way more counterplay than they were supposed to!  8...h6  Black is still hoping to see O-O from White.  9.e4!  ⩲  Avoiding all the ...g5 nonsense! Black is running out of useful moves, and we can simply castle next with a slightly better position thanks to the extra space in the center. }
