{ This is the standard way to castle against the Queen's Indian, and also in general. In some positions White can try to play for long castle, but it's very situational. Now Black has a choice between:  8...d6  8...d5  8...cxd4 @@StartBracket@@the main line@@EndBracket@@. }
8... cxd4 9. exd4 d6 10. Re1
{ I find this to be the most useful move. There is nothing wrong with  10.c3  and it might very well transpose. The reason why I made  10.Re1  the main line is that it's the most flexible move, keeping ideas of c2-c4 ➼ using the Kamsky plan. }
10... Nbd7 11. Bh2
{ This is again, not the only move, but the most flexible one. Starting with  11.c3  is perfectly fine, and it might simply transpose. }
11... Re8
{ After this move we have reached the main crossroads. White has a choice between two big ideas:   12.c3 @@StartBracket@@the standard move@@EndBracket@@  12.a4 @@StartBracket@@the Kamsky plan@@EndBracket@@. }
12. c3
{ This is the most common way of playing and the universal approach for White. In order to be a successful London System player, I think this is one of the structures that you should be looking to master. Instead,  12.a4  a6  13.a5  b5  14.c4  is Kamsky's pet line.Now Black has a choice between two main plans:   12...Bf8 @@StartBracket@@the most common plan@@EndBracket@@  12...Nf8 @@StartBracket@@less common, but quite tricky@@EndBracket@@. }
12... Nf8
{ The main drawback of this plan, compared to  12...Bf8  ,  is that the b6-square will be more vulnerable to Nc4 and a5 ideas. }
13. a4 { Threatening the typical a5. } 13... a6
{ This is usually played automatically with the idea to meet a5 with ...b5! }
14. Nc4 Ng6
{ The most natural way to continue.   14...Nd5  is a better alternative for Black, with the idea to take the b6-square under control. We answer  15.Nfd2  , creating a concrete threat of Ne4 ➼ winning the d6-pawn. After  15...b5  16.axb5  axb5  17.Na3  b4  18.Nb5⩲  White has pressure on the d6-pawn. Just imagine White can play Nc4 on the next move and the pawn is lost. }
15. a5
{ This is the best way to exploit the ...Nf8 plan! The idea is to infiltrate with the knight on b6. }
15... b5
{ Forced because  15...bxa5  16.Nxa5!  will leave Black in a losing position already. }
16. Nb6 Rb8 17. b3
{ Preparing to push c4 on the next move ➼ with pressure on the queenside. White got a quick win in Gual Pascual,A @@StartBracket@@2397@@EndBracket@@-Meylan,A @@StartBracket@@2175@@EndBracket@@ Barcelona 2016. }
