{ 6...a6  prevents Nb5, but the move  7.Qf3!  is incredibly annoying to meet. One point is that after  7...d5  8.Bxb8!  funnily enough, Black is losing the exchange!  8...Rxb8  9.Nc6±  White wins material. }
7. Nb5 { Threatening Nc7+! and eyeing the d6-square. } 7... Nd5
{ The only way to stop Nc7. } 8. Bd6
{ White has a crushing position due to his dominance on the dark squares. } *

