1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4
{ This is the most flexible move order ➼ making sure that we keep everything in London System territory. For more details about the move order make sure to check out the informational. }
2... e6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 b6
{ This move order is a bit inaccurate because it gives White the chance to get an improved version of the Jobava London after  5.Nc3!   Disclaimer: the upcoming lines are very sharp and move by move dependent so you need to be really careful if you are willing to pick this up. Personally I like to keep it simple by going  5.Nbd2  Bb7  6.h3  and just transpose back into the regular lines. }
