{ This is the most precise because  10.Bg2  b4!  gives Black good counterplay. }
10... exd5
{ 10...O-O  gives White an easy game after  11.Bg2  d6  12.O-O  Creating a tactical threat of dxe6 followed by e5!  12...b4  13.Nd1⩲  We will play Ne3 followed by Ndc4 with a much better position for White thanks to the extra space and the juicy square on c4. }
11. e5 { The point! This is very tricky to answer for Black. } 11... Ne4 12.
Ndxe4 dxe4 13. Bg2
{ We can castle short on the next move followed by Nxe4 with a much better position for White. }
