6... b6
{ This move is meant to avoid the 6...c5 7.dxc5 line. Black's plan is pretty simple. The difference compared to the 6...Nbd7 variation is that Black has an additional option of playing with ...Bb7-c5 followed by ...Nc6-Nd7 ➼ delivering the ...e5-break with an equal position. }
7. h4
