[Black "Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Qb6 4. Nc3
{ In this chapter we start by covering the Benoni arising after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.d4  c5  which leads to positions that are no longer a London System + we are also covering the quick ...c5 lines combined with an early ...Qb6!   These lines are also known as the Anti-London because they lead to more complex positions, avoiding White's typical plans. We will split the material between:  •  4...Qxb2   •  4...cxd4   •  4...e6   •  4...d6   •  4...a6   Model games arising from this chapter:  ➡ Grischuk Alexander-Sindarov Javokhir, Online blitz 2020 }
