[Black "1...c5 2.d5 Nf6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 c5 2. d5 Nf6 3. Nc3
{ This works best ➼ keeping the c4-square available for the knight. } 3... e6
4. e4 exd5
{ This is a very common mistake because it's easy to miss White's next move. }
5. e5
{ After this strong intermezzo Black is just lost. The key line is  5...d4  6.exf6  dxc3  7.Qe2+  winning a piece. }
5... Ng8 6. Qxd5 { White has a crushing position. } 6... Nc6 7. Bf4 Nge7 8. Qd2
{ We can continue with O-O-O followed by Nf3 and Black is struggling to finish development. }
