{ Attacking the f4-bishop directly ➼ this can be a very annoying sideline if you are not familiar with it @@StartBracket@@sometimes even if you are!@@EndBracket@@. }
4. Bg3 Qb6
{ Attacking the b2-pawn and keeping an eye on the d4-square. This is probably one of the most annoying anti-Londons. The good news is that I came up with a completely new approach that most black players won't expect. }
5. c4
{ This new exchange sacrifice is the most ambitious way to deal with Black's play and it also gave me a crushing win rate, while I was scoring around 50% with the softer  5.b3  . }
5... Qxb2
{ Going after the exchange ➼ This is what most of my opponents played, and probably what you are going to encounter as well. }
6. cxd5 Qxa1 7. Qc2
{ Trapping Black's queen in the corner while stopping  7...cxd4  because of  8.Qxc8#  . }
7... Na6
{ The most common move for Black in online chess because Black is threatening ...Nb4! }
8. Bxa6
{ This is the simplest way to avoid ...Nb4 and we get quick development. } 8...
bxa6 9. Nf3 { Preparing the standard O-O and Nc3 ➼ trapping Black's queen. }
9... d6 10. Nd2
{ Threatening Nb3! This move works best because  10.O-O  Rb8  would have allowed Black to escape. }
10... Rb8 11. Nb3
{ Attacking the a1-queen. Black has a choice between:  11...Bf5  11...Rxb3. }
11... Bf5
{ Deflecting White's queen with the idea to take the a2-pawn.   11...Rxb3  leads to a slightly better endgame for White:  12.Qxb3  c4  Trying to deflect the queen from defending the b1-knight.  13.Qa4+  This check is useful even though it's not mandatory by any means.  13...Bd7  14.Qc2  c3!  Preparing to escape with ...Qb2 ➼ this is the key idea to save the queen.  15.O-O  Qb2  16.Qxc3  Collecting the pawn and heading for a slightly better endgame.  16...Qxc3  17.Nxc3⩲  With Rb1-Rb8 coming White has the initiative in this endgame. }
12. Qxf5 Qxa2 13. N1d2
{ The knight is yet untouchable because of  13...Rxb3  14.Qc8#! } 13... c4 14.
Nc5 { Threatening Qd7#. } 14... Rd8 15. Ne6
{ This is the only move to keep advantage, but that advantage is pretty large!  15...fxe6  16.dxe6  is much better for White after  16...Rb8  and the simple  17.O-O  because the enemy king is weak. }
