[SetUp "1"]

1... Qc7
{ This is a very common line for Black ➼ trying for the quick ...Nbd7 followed by ...e5! }
2. Bxd6
{ This is by far the best!   2.Bg3  This would be exactly what Black wants to see.  2...Nbd7=  With ...e5 coming next and Black has full equality.   2.Ne5  This is a playable alternative, but not fighting for an edge.  2...Nc6  3.Ndf3  Ne7∞  Black is going to play ... cxd4 followed by ...Ne4 with an equal game. }
2... Qxd6 3. Ne5
{ Centralizing the knight and preparing to support it with f4! } 3... Nbd7 4.
f4
{ After this important move White secures a free advantage without any risks. Black's position is simply very uncomfortable. }
